d the way for the emergence of a distinctively non-Western form of religious pluralism. This work provides a critical resource for understanding how Hinduism developed in the early modern period, a crucial era that set the tenor for religion's role in public life in India through the present day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aRELIGION / Hinduism / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066755440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520966291?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966291zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520966291/original  a978-3-11-064982-6 Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066755-4 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA